D-Modem
=======

D-Modem is a software SIP modem developed by Aon plc's cyber labs,
published at https://github.com/synexo/D-Modem (the synexo fork that
tracks PJSIP 2.15).

synthmodem vendors one file from D-Modem, `d-modem.c`, at
`vm/d-modem/d-modem.c`. This file is a PJSIP `pjmedia_port` subclass
that bridges a PJSIP audio call to slmodemd's socketpair; it is the
integration layer the `slmodemd-pjsip` backend relies on.

synthmodem does NOT vendor:

  - D-Modem's bundled `pjproject-2.15.1/` subtree. We verified at
    vendor time that this subtree is byte-identical to upstream
    pjsip/pjproject at tag 2.15.1, so we vendor PJSIP directly from
    the upstream source (see licenses/PJSIP-NOTICE).
  - D-Modem's bundled `slmodemd/` subtree. synthmodem already vendors
    slmodemd at `vm/slmodemd/` from an earlier pin of the same
    upstream; that coverage is unchanged.

Upstream project:  https://github.com/synexo/D-Modem
Upstream branch:   pjsip2.15
Pinned commit:     902c79aa36fa094c7513fa911b64f4fa8a0bf614

